text.raa.item.lexicon.name: RAA Lexicon
text.raa.item.lexicon.landing: This lexicon will give information about materials, dimensions and dimension materials whenever you discover/mine them
text.autoconfig.raa.title: Options: Générales
config.field.raa.biomeData.name: Nom du Biome :
config.field.raa.biomeData.surfaceBuilde: Chance de variation du constructeur de surface :
config.tooltip.raa.lush:
Lush dimensions have an abundance of
trees, vegetation and plants.
config.tooltip.raa.civilized:
Civilized dimensions have structures
left behind by old civilizations.
config.tooltip.raa.dead:
Dead dimensions have no plants or animals;
the only trees you will find are fossilized.
config.tooltip.raa.abandoned:
Abandoned dimensions have a few generic
structures left behind by explorers and civilizations.
config.tooltip.raa.molten: Molten dimensions have lava oceans. Good luck!
config.tooltip.raa.dry:
Dry dimensions don't have any oceans.
The only water is in pools.
config.tooltip.raa.tectonic:
Tectonic dimensions have an abundance of
caves and ravines. Don't fall in!
config.tooltip.raa.corrupted:
Corrupted dimensions have netherrack and fire,
randomly jutting into the landscape. Have fun!
